<P>
<B>Conclusion</B>
<P>
Thermocouples are inexpensive temperature sensing devices that
are widely used with PCbased DAQ systems. Thermocouple measurement
requires signal conditioning, including cold-junction compensation,
amplification, and linearization. The National Instruments SCXI
signal conditioning system is a low-noise front end for PCbased
DAQ systems when you use thermocouples to measure temperature.
<P>
<B>References</B>
<P>
