<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2>S</FONT>tandards<BR></CENTER>

<HR>
<a href="http://www.yahoo.com/Reference/Standards/">Yahoo List of sights<BR>

<a href="http://www.ansi.org/">American National Standards Institute</a><BR>
<a href="/Computers_and_Internet/Standards/"><b>Computers@</b></a> <i>(28)</i><BR>
<a href="http://www.hike.te.chiba-u.ac.jp/iec417/index.html">Graphical Symbols Compliant to IEC Standard 417</a><BR>
<a href="/Business_and_Economy/Organizations/Science_and_Technology/International_Organization_for_Standardization__ISO_/"><b>International Organization for Standardization (ISO)@</b></a> <i>(3)</i><BR>
<a href="http://www.mcrel.org/standards-benchmarks/docs/std-ben.html">Standards and Benchmarks</a><BR>
<a href="http://www-atp.llnl.gov/standards.html">Standards Documentation</a> - This list contains links to the most useful computer and communication related standards information that we have found on the Internet.<BR>
<a href="http://www.bldrdoc.gov/doc-tour/atomic_clock.html">Time - Boulder, CO</a> - Department of Commerce's atomic clock timeserver<BR>
<a href="gopher://india.colorado.edu:13/0">Time - National Institute of Standards and Technology</a> - Current Time<BR>
<a href="http://www.nyu.edu/pages/psychology/WEAPAS/">Web Extention to American Psychological Association Style</a> - Proposed standard for referencing online documents in scientific publications.<BR>
<a href="http://www.iso.ch/VL/Standards.html">Index - Standards and Standardization Bodies - WWW Virtual Library</a><BR>
</ul>

