<html>
<head>
   <title>Craig van Rij BE(Hons)</title>
   <meta name="GENERATOR" content="Mozilla/2.01Gold (Win32)">
   <meta name="Author" content="Craig van Rij">
</head>
<body text="#000000" bgcolor="#C0C0C0" link="#0000EE" vlink="#551A8B" alink="#FF0000" background="rivits.gif">
<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML 3.0//EN" "html.dtd">
<h1 align=center>Craig van Rij <font SIZE=+2>BE(hons)</font></h1>

<p><img src="mecvr.jpg" alt="Photo of me at my desk" border=0 height=201 width=300 align=right><b><font SIZE=+1>Mechanical
Engineering,</font></b></p>

<p><b><font SIZE=+1>University of Canterbury, N.Z</font></b><font SIZE=+2>.</font></p>

<p>Hi, my name is Craig van Rij. I am a PhD student in the Mechanical Engineering
department. My work is in the <a href="http://www.mech.canterbury.ac.nz/research/SE.htm">Stirling
Engine Group</a> working with Stirling Cycle engines for RAPS&nbsp;type
applications. Specifically my research is concerned with the <a href="http://www.mech.canterbury.ac.nz/student/postgrad/cvrphd.htm">optimization
of the combustion</a> systems for these engines.</p>

<p>My main field of interest is in mechanical engineering design and CAD.
I do all of my design work using Microstation and Modeler from Bentley
and enjoy using computers for the majority of my work. I have spent the
last 12 months designing and building a 3kW generator set based on the
earlier work done on 200W Stirling engines within this department.</p>

<p>I live here in Christchurh with my wife Veronica who is at the College
of Education doing Secondary school training.</p>

<CENTER><hr SIZE = "2" WIDTH = "90%" ALIGN = "LEFT"></a><font SIZE=-2>http://www.mech.canterbury.ac.nz/student/postgrad/vanrijcw.htm
| 15 July 1996 
<br>[<a href="http://www.canterbury.ac.nz/">UOC Home</a>] [<a href="http://www.mech.canterbury.ac.nz/">Mech
Home</a>] [<a href="mailto:vanrijcw@mech.canterbury.ac.nz">EMail</a>] [<a href="#top">Top</a>]
[<a href="/index.htm">Back</a>]</font> 
<br><img src="/images/star.gif" border=0 >
<br></p></CENTER>

</body>
</html>
