<body>

<h1>
	Karen's Organized Hotlist
</h1>

<hr>

<i>
Last updated: 
12 October 1995
</i>

<hr>

I use George Xie's
<a href="http://www.ugrad.cs.ubc.ca/spider/q7f192/branch/checker.html">Anchor
Checker</a> to check the ``liveness'' of the URLs in this page.

<hr>

<em>
I enjoy hearing that other people find this page useful or
entertaining.  However, it was originally meant as my personal list of
links I'd like to find again for some reason or other.  It isn't
something that was meant to help companies or random people advertise
their pages.  I enjoy the nice ego-boost of ``Hey! I like your page.
You might like &lt;blah&gt;.  It's bizarre.'' But things like ``Please
add my page &lt;blah&gt; to your database.'' just annoy me. 
</em>

<hr>
