<H4><A NAME="main_extrusion">A main base protrusion (Extrusion):</A></H4>
__ . . .

<!-- . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . -->
<H4><A NAME="rear_holes">A pair of rear `pip' holes (Extruded Cut):</A></H4>
__ . . .

<!-- . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . -->
<H4><A NAME="base_recess">A square recess in the foot (Extruded Cut):</A></H4>
__ . . .

<!-- . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . -->
<H4><A NAME="pivot_hole">A pivot hole (Extruded Cut):</A></H4>
__ . . .

<!-- . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . -->
<H4><A NAME="surface_rebate">A surface rebate (Extruded Cut):</A></H4>
__ . . .

<P><A HREF="#start">Return to Contents at the start of this document ? <IMG ALIGN=top SRC="back.gif"></A>

<!------------------------------------------------------------------------->
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="submit">SUBMITTING THIS PART FOR ASSESSMENT:</A></H3>

When you have modelled your `leg_r' part as far as you intend, you should
submit it for assessment by your tutor.  To do this, you must save a copy
of it to the special directory which has been set up for you in the common
area of the computer's filesystem.  This directory has the same name as your
login name.  For example, if your login name is `jsmith', then you must save
the part to the directory named <KBD>/home/common/me/ge1/jsmith</KBD>.<P>

If you have finished your `leg_r' part for the time being, submit it for
assessment now by following these instructions (you can always re-submit
it again later if you improve your part).  Beginning from the MAIN menu,
select <B>Dbms -&gt; Backup</B>.  You will be prompted for the name of a
directory into which Pro/ENGINEER will save a copy of your part (the
default offered will be your current working directory).  In response to
the prompt, type:
<P><KBD>Which directory ? [...]: <B>/home/common/me/ge1/</B></KBD><I>yourname</I><KBD><B> &lt;CR&gt;</B></KBD><P>
... of course replacing `<I>yourname</I>' with your own login name.<P>

Ensure that the object to be saved is the `leg_r' (it should be the default
offered in the message window -- if so, then just type a <B>&lt;CR&gt;</B>
at the prompt).  You will see a reassuring comment if Pro/ENGINEER can
successfully store your part in the desired location.  If not, then please
<EM>consult your tutor</EM>.

<P><A HREF="#start">Return to Contents at the start of this document ? <IMG ALIGN=top SRC="back.gif"></A>

<HR>
<!------------------------------------------------------------------------->
