<HEAD>
<TITLE>Exercise GE1: GEOMETRIC MODELLING -- ARMS OF A LEGO(tm) PERSON</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<H1>Exercise GE1 (cont.): ... LEGO(tm) ARMS</H1>

<!-- next filename.gif should have same stem as present filename.html -->
<IMG SRC="arms.gif">
<HR>
<!-- next nextfile.html must match next file in series -->
<A HREF="lego_hand.html"><IMG SRC="skip.gif"></A><P>

<H2><A NAME="start">Contents (`ARMS of a LEGO person'):</A></H2>
<OL>
<LI><A HREF="#started">GETTING STARTED</A>
<LI><A HREF="#oview">OVERVIEW OF THE ARM PARTS (arm_r and arm_l)</A>
</OL>

<!------------------------------------------------------------------------->
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="started">GETTING STARTED:</A></H3>

The modelling of arms for a LEGO person is beyond the scope of this
exercise, since it requires the use of some of Pro/ENGINEER's more advanced
capabilities.  Nevertheless, you may be interested to retrieve a copy of 
some sample arm parts which we have created for you.  Assuming your earlier
models have been created using Pro/ENGINEER's `millimetre base unit' (which
will be true if you have copied the <KBD>config.pro</KBD> file correctly
into your home directory), then these arm parts should be compatible with
your own LEGO parts.<P>

There is of course no need to submit an `arm' part for assessment.<P>

Before you retrieve any new part, ensure that you have saved previous work
in the current Pro/ENGINEER session (by selecting <B>Dbms -&gt; Save</B>
from the MAIN menu, and typing a <B>&lt;CR&gt;</B> to accept the proposed
name).  This might also be a good time to get rid of all the out-dated 
versions of the part you have just finished, so that disk space is not
wasted.  If that part is still current, just select <B>Dbms -&gt; Purge</B>
from the MAIN menu, and type a <B>&lt;CR&gt;</B> to accept the default. 
The <B>Purge</B> command is quite safe -- it leaves you with only the
latest version of your part file.<P>

If the previous part you were working on is to be submitted for
assessment, you should also save a copy of it to your special `submission'
directory by selecting <B>Dbms -&gt; Backup</B> and typing in the full
pathname of your submission directory (refer to the handout sheet entitled 
<EM>Assessment of Work in Exercise GE1</EM> for more complete instructions
on how to do this).<P>

Then clear the graphics window by selecting <B>Quit Window</B> from the 
MAIN menu.  The MODE menu should appear beneath the MAIN menu.<P>

To retrieve a copy of the right arm, select <B>Part -$gt; Retrieve</B> from
the MODE menu, and type the following pathname into the message window:<P>

<KBD><B>/home/common/pro/arm_r &lt;CR&gt;</B></KBD><P>

If desired, the left arm part can be retrieved by a similar process from:<P>

<KBD><B>/home/common/pro/arm_l &lt;CR&gt;</B></KBD><P>

<!------------------------------------------------------------------------->
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="oview">OVERVIEW OF THE ARM PARTS (arm_r and arm_l):</A></H3>

__Overview blurb.

<P><A HREF="#start">Return to Contents at the start of this document ? <IMG ALIGN=top SRC="back.gif"></A>

