<H1>Exercise CG2: CLOSURE</H1>

<!-- next filename.gif should have same stem as present filename.html -->
<IMG SRC="closure.gif.html">
<HR>

<H2><A NAME="start">Contents (`CLOSURE'):</A></H2>
<OL>
<LI><A HREF="#review">Review of Exercise CG2</A>
<LI><A HREF="#__internal_name">__SORRY</A>
</OL>

<!------------------------------------------------------------------------->
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="review">Review of Exercise CG2:</A></H3>

Exercise CG2 has provided a brief introduction to computer-based geometric
modelling. You have constructed a single part consisting of a number of
`features'.  The shape of the part was suggestive of a steel bracket -- the
sort which might be bolted to a wall to form a ladder rung.  In a sense,
though, the shape of the bracket was unimportant, as long as it possessed
a sufficiently interesting geometry to require several geometric features.

<P><A HREF="#start">Return to Contents at the start of this document ? <IMG ALIGN=top SRC="back.gif"></A>

<!------------------------------------------------------------------------->
<HR>
