<P><KBD>Enter Part name [PRT0001]: <B>leg_r &lt;CR&gt;</B></KBD><P>

<!------------------------------------------------------------------------->
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="oview">OVERVIEW OF THIS PART (the leg_r):</A></H3>

The legs of a LEGO person have a surprisingly intricate internal shape, 
largely because they have been hollowed out to save plastic and to facilitate
the plastic moulding process.  For the sake of this exercise, you need not
represent all of the internal geometry in detail.<P>

Also note that the left leg and the right leg are mirror images of each
other.  We will exploit this symmetry when we create the second leg.  These
instructions assume that you are modelling the right leg first.

__Overview blurb.

<P><A HREF="#start">Return to Contents at the start of this document ? <IMG ALIGN=top SRC="back.gif"></A>

<!------------------------------------------------------------------------->
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="feats_outline">BRIEF OUTLINE OF FEATURES FOR `leg_r':</A></H3>

There are many ways to model the `leg_r' part.  One suggested approach is
to use the following set of features:
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="#datum_planes">A default set of Datum Planes</A>
<LI><A HREF="#main_extrusion">A main base protrusion (Extrusion)</A>
<LI><A HREF="#rear_holes">A pair of rear `pip' holes (Extruded Cut)</A>
<LI><A HREF="#base_recess">A square recess in the foot (Extruded Cut)</A>
<LI><A HREF="#pivot_hole">A pivot hole (Extruded Cut)</A>
<LI><A HREF="#surface_rebate">A surface rebate (Extruded Cut)</A>
</UL>

<!-- . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . -->
<H4><A NAME="datum_planes">A default set of Datum Planes:</A></H4>
__ . . .

<!-- . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . -->
<H4><A NAME="main_extrusion">A main base protrusion (Extrusion):</A></H4>
__ . . .

<!-- . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . -->
<H4><A NAME="rear_holes">A pair of rear `pip' holes (Extruded Cut):</A></H4>
__ . . .

<!-- . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . -->
