<html>
<head>
<title>17. Don't Blink</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<H5><I>Writing HTML</I> |
<A HREF="index2.html">About</A> | <A HREF="faq.html">FAQ</A> |
<A HREF="http://www.mcli.dist.maricopa.edu/cgi-bin/alumni.pl">Alumni</A> |
<A HREF="tag2.html">Tags</A> |
<A HREF="lessons.html">Index</A> |
<A HREF="tut16.html">back</A> | 
<A HREF="tut18.html">next</A> </H5>

<h1>17. Don't Blink!</h1>
Are you trying to attract attention to your web pages? Rely on compelling <b>content</b> rather than <blink>cheap</blink> attention grabbers...

<h2>Objectives</h2>
After this lesson you will:
<ul>
<li>Never use the blink tag.
</ul>
<hr>

<h2>Lesson</h2>
When NetScape first unveiled their web browser they added a unique tag that would ostensibly draw attention to an important word or phrase- by causing it to flash on and off in the web page.
<p>
The dreaded blink tag:
<PRE>  &lt;blink&gt;Wow&lt;/blink&gt;</PRE>
is a sign that well-travelled web surfers take as <font size=+1><TT><B>"avoid this page- the person that wrote it just learned HTML from a bubble gum wrapper."</B></TT></font><p> Short of an extremely urgent reason to use it, avoid at all costs something that looks like:
<center>
<table border=1 cellpadding=16 cellspacing=12>
<tr>
<td align=center valign=middle>
<blink><font color=#BB0000 size=+3>T</font><font color=#BB0000 size=+2>h</font><font  color=#BB0000 size=+4><B>i</B></font><font color=#BB0000 size=+2>s</font></blink> <font size=+1><I>is</I></font> &nbsp; the <blink><font size=+4><B><I><font color=#DD11BB>HOTTEST</font></I></B></font></blink><blink><font color=#0033DD size=+3> place</font></blink> 
<font size=+2>ON THE </font>
<blink><font color=#0099DD size=+3>Web </font></blink>
</td></tr>
</table>
</center>
<p>
<basefont=+3>
Unless you are building the <TT><B><font color=#FF00EE>sleaze</font></B></TT>  row of web pages...

<h2>Coming Next....</h2>


<h5>  GO TO....  | <A HREF="lessons.html">Lesson Index</A> | 
<A HREF="tut16.html">back:  "Backgrounds"</A> |
<A HREF="tut18.html">next:  "Spiffing Up text"</A> |
</h5>
<HR>
<b>Writing HTML</b>  Lesson 17: Don't Blink<br>
