<hr>
<h2>Check Your Work</h2>
Compare your web page with a <a href="http://hakatai.mcli.dist.maricopa.edu/tut/tut8c_ex/index.html">sample</a>
of how this document should appear. If your
web page was different than the sample or the links do not
properly connect to a remote site, review the text you entered in the
text editor. Note that your list of references may be different from
the example.

<h2>Review Topics</h2>
<ol>
<li>What is the address for an item on the Internet? 
<li>What steps did you take for creating an anchor link to the NASA
Internet Site?
<li>What shortcut was identified for putting an URL into an anchor
link?
<li>Tell a neighbor about any other Internet anchor links that you
put in your document.
</ol>
<h2>Independent Practice</h2>
Create anchor links from your own web page that connect to
some of the URLs addresses you have discovered.
<hr>
