<h1>UCant Dance - Events</h1>

<h2>1996</h2>

<dt><b>Orientation Party (Thursday 22 February)</b></dt>

<dd>Not bad for a Thursday night! We managed to pack the Upper Common Room
with keen dancers and those that drifted up from the main event in the
Ballroom to escape the bone crushing noise. 
<br></dd>

<dt><b><a href="http://www.mech.canterbury.ac.nz/clubs/latindnc/hanmer.htm">Hanmer
Weekend Trip</a> (11-12 May)</b></dt>

<dd>Twenty latin dancers descended on Hanmer Springs for the weekend in
May. The nice people at the Hanmer Springs Forest Camp Trust let us hold
a very noisy dance party in their dining hall. A couple of dips in the
hot springs and a BBQ plus some outdoorsy type running around kept us all
occupied. 
<br></dd>

<dt><b>Term 3 End of Term Party (Thursday, August 15)</b></dt>

<dd>As part of the end-of-term stein we kept the Lower Common Room rocking
while the Puffins played upstairs. Our mix of dance and latin music went
down quite well with a crowd who weren't familiar with Merengue and thought
Salsa is a sauce. 
<br></dd>

<dt><b>Latin Love Boat Break Up Party (Saturday, November 9)</b></dt>

<dd>With the aid of a fishing net, a rubber life raft, and oodles of cardboard
fish, the break up party was an event to remember. Dug into the coffers
and rented some heavy duty party gear including a strobe light and 400W
Jands amp. More grunt than a copulating pig! Now there's a pleasant image.
An impromptu Tango lesson and Pinata made for interesting distractions.
</dd>

<h2>1997</h2>

<dt><b>Orientation Party &quot;The UCant Dance Party&quot;</b></dt>

<dd>Hoping for another ripper this year. Thursday, 6 March, 8.30pm in the
Lower Common Room. The main event in the Ballroom will be the 3Ds and there
will be a fashion show in the Upper Common Room. Entry to the &quot;UCant
Dance Party&quot; will be by single night ticket or orientation ticket.
Orientation events are open to students and partners only.</dd>

<p><a href="http://www.mech.canterbury.ac.nz/clubs/latindnc/latindnc.htm">Home
</a></p>

</body>
