<h1>Andrew Lintott (BE Hons)</h1>

<h4>Personal Details</h4>

<pre>Full name:      Andrew Brent Lintott
Date of birth:  11 October, 1969
Citizenship:    New Zealand
Marital status: Single
Qualifications: Bachelor's degree BE MECH (Hons), (conferred 1992),
                School of Engineering, Canterbury University</pre>

<h4>Experience</h4>

<ul>
<li>1992present Currently completing Doctor of Philosophy degree in Mechanical
Engineering at Canterbury University.</li>

<li>1992present Octa Associates Ltd (Project management consultants) CAD
draughting, computer systems maintenance, software development and customisation.</li>

<li>1990present Self-employed (Part time) Laying of cobblestone driveways.
</li>

<li>Dec 1989Feb 1990 Electrical Control Systems Ltd Fitting and turning,
welding, and assembly of automatic feeders for industrial dough mixers.
</li>

<li>JanFeb 1989 Spheronic Developments Ltd (Vacation work) All aspects
of the lost wax casting process. </li>
</ul>

<h4>Other Qualifications</h4>

<ul>
<li>Driver's license</li>

<li>Red Cross first aid certificate. </li>
</ul>

<h4>Hobbies and Interests:</h4>

<ul>
<li>Ballroom Dance Regular social and competitive dancer since 1989. </li>

<li>19941996 President, University of Canterbury Latin Dance Club Activities:
Club administration, dance instruction, and organising and overseeing club
events. Founding member. </li>

<li>1995 Chairman, Christchurch Ballroom Dancing Club Activities: Club
administration, meeting chair. Choreographer and dance performer Local
Repertory theatre production &quot;Broadway Follies&quot;. </li>

<li>Luthiery (Guitar making and repair) Have made a number of electric
guitars from scratch. Have also built several amplifiers from 30 to 100
Watts. </li>

<li>Swimming Recently learnt to swim. Now a regular swimmer for fitness.
</li>
</ul>

</body>
