<h1><b>ROBOTICS AND CONTROL<br><p></b></h1>

<IMG SRC="robot.JPG"><br>

The above robot is being developed for driving an antenna dish. This particular
robot is known as a parallel robot since there are multiple connections between the
moveable platform at the top and the base. Parallel robots are becoming
increasingly popular as they offer advantages over traditional serial robots, such as
higher lifting forces and greater stiffness. This is one of several parallel robots
being designed and investigated by the Department of Mechanical Engineering.<br><p>

Students also have the opportunity of learning computer and micro-processor
control, pneumatics and hydraulics. Mechanical and electrical stability of systems
are also studied.<br><p>
</DOC>
