<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>Publications</H1>

<H3>THESES </H3>

<UL>
<P>WARD D.K.(1996) &quot;<I>Design of a Two Degree of Freedom Robotic Finger</I>&quot;,
ME thesis, University of Canterbury, Christchurch, New Zealand. </P>

<P>DANN A.J. (1996) <I>Automated guided vehicle control and stability</I>,
ME thesis in preparation, University of Canterbury, Christchurch, New Zealand.
</P>

<P>HOYLE W J (1996) <I>Fuzzy logic, control, and optimisation</I> ME thesis,
University of Canterbury, Christchurch, New Zealand. </P>

<P>Hampson S P (1995) <I>Nonlinear predictive control of a hydraulic actuator</I>,
PhD thesis, University of Canterbury, Christchurch, New Zealand. </P>

<P>Kuang Yan (1995) Going from an intelligent tutoring system for control
engineering to tools for teaching, ME thesis, University of Canterbury,
Christchurch, New Zealand. </P>

<P>Rayudu R K (1994) An expert assistant for hydraulic power computer aided
engineering, ME thesis, University of Canterbury, Christchurch, New Zealand.
</P>

<P>O'Brien D N (1994) Brushless DC motor control, ME thesis, University
of Canterbury, Christchurch, New Zealand.</P>

<P>Afzulpurkar N V (1990) Kinematics, design, programming and control of
a robotic platform for satellite tracking and other applications, PhD thesis,
University of Canterbury, Christchurch, New Zealand.</P>

<P>Ma Li (1989) Multi axis numerical control, ME thesis, University of
Canterbury, Christchurch, New Zealand.</P>

<P>Marvelly J D 1986 Position encoderless self synchronisation of variable
reluctance stepping motors, ME thesis, University of Canterbury, Christchurch,
New Zealand. (ME awarded with distinction.)</P>
</UL>

<P>Rathbun G 1985 A Stewart platform six-axis milling machine development,
ME thesis, University of Canterbury, Christchurch, New Zealand.</P>

<P>Pearson W D 1982 A microcomputer numerically controlled milling centre,
ME thesis, University of Canterbury, Christchurch, New Zealand.</P>

<H3>REFEREED PUBLICATIONS AND KEYNOTE PAPERS</H3>

<P>Hampson SP, Sirisena H R and Dunlop G R 1995 Model predictive control
of a hydraulic actuator, Proc. SICICI'95, IEEE Singapore International
Conf. on Intelligent Control, Singapore, July 3-7, Vol 1 pp396-401.</P>

<P>Raine J K, Whybrew K, Dunlop G R, van Rij C W and Ward D K 1995 Redesign
and manufacture of the Feltex Jacquard loom card punch system, Proc. Int.
Conf. on Engineering Design ICED'95, Prague, Czech Republic, Aug 22-24,
Vol 2 pp684-691.</P>

<P>Dunlop G R and Ward D K 1995 The kinematics of a fifteen DOF six fingered
hand, Proc. Ninth World Congress on the Theory of Machines and Mechanisms
IFToMM, Milan, Italy, Aug. 30 - Sept. 2, Vol 3 pp2249-2253.</P>

<P>Dunlop G R 1995 Cost-performance cell configuration trade-offs for robot
palletizing. Int. J. Robotics &amp; Automation, Vol 10 No 1 pp18-21.</P>

<P>Dunlop G R and Hampson S P 1994 An integrated digital control system
for hydraulic actuators, Proc. Seventh Bath International Fluid Power Workshop,
Bath, U.K., Sept. 21-23, R.S.P. John Wiley &amp; Sons Inc., ISBN0 471 95688
0, Ch 13 pp177-186.</P>

<P>Dunlop G R and Hampson S P 1994 An integrated digital control system
for hydraulic actuators, Proc. Seventh Bath International Fluid Power Workshop,
Bath, U.K., Sept. 21-23, R.S.P. John Wiley &amp; Sons Inc., ISBN0 471 95688
0, Ch 13 pp177-186.</P>

<P>Dunlop G R 1994 A switched reluctance motor drive with zero torque ripple
and a constant inverter bus current, Proc. IMechE part1 JSCE, Vol 208 pp61-68.</P>

<P>Dunlop G R, Ellis P J and Afzulpurkar 1993 The satellite tracking keyhole
problem: a parallel mechanism mount solution, IPENZ Trans, Vol 20 No 1/EMCh
pp1-7.</P>

<P>Dunlop G R and Rayudu R K 1993 An expert design assistant for hydraulic
systems. Proceedings of The First New Zealand International Two-Stream
Conference on Artificial Neural Networks and Expert Systems, Ed. Nikola
K Kasabov, IEEE Computer Society Press, ISBN 0-8186-4260-2 pp314-316.</P>

<P>Dunlop G R and Hampson S P 1993 Bond graphs for nonlinear modeling of
an electro-hydraulic system, Proc. of the Int. Congress MV2 - Active Control
in Mechanical Engineering, Lyon, France, Tome 1 pp62-72.</P>

<P>Whybrew K, Raine J K, Dunlop G R and Overbye H 1993 An articulated geometry
skid tractor AGV, Int. J. Adv. Manuf. Technol., Vol 8 No 2 pp111-113.</P>

<P>Dunlop G R, Lintott A B and Jones T P 1992 Linear and spherical robots
with three DOF, Proc. First Australian Workshop on the Theories of Machines
and Mechanisms, Ed. Andrew Samuel, University of Melbourne Press, ISBN
0-7325-0594-1, Melbourne, Australia, AWToMM'92 pp175-202.</P>

<P>Dunlop G R 1992 Cell configuration trade-offs for robot setting of refractory
bricks, Proc. IASTED Int. Conf. on Control and Robotics, Vancouver, Canada,
Vol 1 pp121-124.</P>

<P>Hampson S and Dunlop G R 1992 Digital controlled hydraulic rig suitable
for teaching advanced control theory, IPENZ Trans Vol 19 No 1/EMCh pp28-33.</P>

<CENTER><P>Afzulpurkar N V, Graham I and Dunlop G R 1991 Kinematic analysis
of a closed link robotic mechanism using a transputer network, The Transputer
in Australia 2, Eds. Hulskamp, Bossommaier and Hintz, IOS Press, pp1-6.</P></CENTER>

<P>Dunlop G R, Johnson G R and Afzulpurkar N V 1991 Joint design for extended
range Stewart platform applications, Proc. Eighth World Congress on the
Theory of Machines and Mechanisms, Prague, Czechoslovakia, Vol 2 pp449-451.</P>

<P>Dunlop G R 1990 Simple step motor control for multi axis positioning,
Proc. PEMC'90, Conference on Power Electronics and Motion Control, Budapest,
Hungary, Oct. 1-3, Vol 2 pp424-428.</P>

<P>Dunlop G R, Chen Renlu and Duke R M 1990 An experimental constant current
computer controlled invertor for constant torque switched reluctance motors,
Proc. of the Electric Drive Symposium, EDS'90, Capri, Vol 2 pp173-179.</P>

<P>Afzulpurkar N V and Dunlop G R 1989 A novel antenna mount for orbital
satellite tracking and marine communications. Fifth National Space Engineering
Symposium, Canberra, Australia, Nov.27-Dec.1. The Institute of Engineers
Australia Publication No 89/20 pp92-96.</P>

<P>Dunlop G R 1989 Communications systems for remote construction sites,
Proc. First IES Information Technology Conference, Singapore, May 25-27,
Vol 1 pp178-184.</P>

<P>Dunlop G R 1988 Power device reduction using negative torque sequences
in switched reluctance motors, Proc. Int. Conf. on Electrical Machines,
ICEM'88, Pisa, Italy, Sept. 12-14, Vol 2 pp595-598.</P>



