<H1><B><align=left>GREENPEACE TOXICS PAGE</B></H1></head></align=left></center>
<img WIDTH=560 HEIGHT=29 src="icons/forest.gif" 
alt="-------------------------------------------------------------">
<br>Welcome to the <B>The Greenpeace toxics page</B>, where you can find information on 
our toxics campaigns. Click on the icons to visit other Greenpeace sites. Read <a 
href="navigate.html">how to use the navigator</a> or read the <a href="key.html">key to icons</a>.<P><P><HR>
<P><b>CURRENT  INTERNATIONAL CAMPAIGNS:</b>

<P><a href="/~comms/toxics/dumping/"><img src="icons/dumpt.gif" align="center"  border=0 alt="Dumping" width=28 height=28></a> <a href="/~comms/toxics/dumping">Shell's proposals for Brent Spar:</a> 21 out of 29 are ok, Greenpeace tells London conference.

<P><a href="~comms/ken/"><img wiDTH=28 HEIGHT=28 align="center"  SRC="icons/shellket.gif" ALT="Nigeria: " border=0></a>
Shell in Ogoniland - testimony of <a href="~comms/ken/">Owens Wiwa</a> (Ken Saro's brother)

<p><a href="/~comms/brent/brent.html"><img src="icons/sshe.gif" align="center"  border=0 alt="Brent Spar" width=28 height=28></A>  Don't Dump the Brent Spar action in the North Sea and new <a href="/~comms/brent/brent.html">press release on pollution of an aquifer in Turkey</A>


<HR>
<P><b>CURRENT NATIONAL CAMPAIGNS:</b>

<P><a href="/~uk/science"><img align=center src="/~uk/science/icons/ner0.gif" border=0 width=28 height=28>Greenpeace UK Science site </a>opens with a discussion on <a href="/~uk/science/hdc"><img align=center src="/~uk/science/icons/swimmer5.gif" border=0 width=36 height=18></a> hormone disrupting chemicals.

<P><a href="http://www.web.apc.org/~embargo/"><img src="/icons/canken.gif" width=42 height=28 align=bottom border=0 alt="GP Canada Shell Oil Embargo"></a>Greenpeace Canada are running a <a href="http://www.web.apc.org/~embargo/">"Fax the Feds"</a> Shell oil embargo campaign.

