<TITLE>non-Greenpeace environmental sources</TITLE>
<LINK REV="MADE" HREF="sysop@xs2.greenpeace.org">
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor=#FFFFFF>
<h2>Other WWW sources:</h2>
<p>
The following list of WWW sources are just provided for general interest. It does in no
way reflect whether the information therein is endorsed by Greenpeace or
not. It is not meant to be exhaustive; some of the sites below provide
 more elaborate listings.<br>
For instance, have a look at:

<ul>
<li>the <A HREF="http://www.webdirectory.com/">Amazing Environmental 
Organization WebDirectory</A>, with a 
<a href="http://www.webdirectory.com/survey_results.html">survey</a> where 
Greenpeace was voted the most popular environmental organisation.
</li>
<li>the directory in <a 
href="http://www.wnia.org/WNIA/directory.html">What's New In Activism</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.igc.apc.org/igc/issues.html">IGC's issues page</a></li>
<li><a href="http://lablinks.com/sumeria/">Sumeria</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.contact.org/">Contact Center Network Global Nonprofit Directory</a>, 
(NYC)</li>
<li><A HREF="www.ulb.ac.be/ceese/cds.html">Directory of Best Environmental 
Directories</a> (Europe)</li>

</ul>
It is taking too much of my time to maintain the list below, so there is quite a 
backlog. Many links may be outdated by now. Use them at your own peril!<br>
For more up-to-date links, please refer to the directories listed above.
</p><p></p>

<h2>Other NGOs and institutes:</h2>
<ul>
<li> <A HREF="http://www.redbay.com/redpel/">The Redberry Pelican Project</A> &nbspfocuses on fish-eating colonial nesting birds.
</li>

<li> <A HREF="http://www.igc.apc.org/">The Progressive Directory @IGC</A> (Econet)</li>
<li> <A HREF="http://www.lsi.usp.br/econet/econet.htm">Econet (Brasil)</a></li>
<li> <A HREF="http://netzwww.zdv.uni-tuebingen.de/gaia.html">Gaia Ev. in 
Germany</a>, Environmental BBS, Tuebingen</li>
<li> <A HREF="http://www.the-body-shop.com/action.html"><b>Act Now!</b> 
Trial in Nigeria</A> of <b>Ken Saro-Wiwa</b> (Ogoni people)</li>
<li> <a href="http://www.nigeria.com/hy-nigeria/get/boards/ken.html">Book 
of condolences for Ken</a></li>
<li> <a href="http://www.communicopia.bc.ca">Communicopia</a> (Canada)</li>
<li> <A HREF="http://www.foe.co.uk/">Friends of the Earth</A> (UK)</li>
