<title>Nuclear Waste Shipment</title></head>

<body !--background="../icons/nukbac5b.gif"-- bgcolor="#FFBC2A" text="#000000" link="#008000" alink= "#000099" vlink="#139000">

<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 CELLSPACING=0 WIDTH=600>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN=TOP>
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=7><TR><TD WIDTH=480 ALIGN=LEFT>
<FONT SIZE=+1 FACE="MS SERIF">P L U T O N I U M &nbsp W A S T E &nbspS H I P M E N T</FONT>
</TD>
<TD><img width=10 height=1 border=0 src="../icons/tinyb.gif"></TD>
<TD WIDTH=40>
<A HREF="trans.html" onMouseOver="moveover('Back to Transport Main Page'); return true"><img valign=middle width=45 height=36 border=0 src="../icons/ntransh.gif" alt="Transport"></a>
</TD>


</TR></TABLE>
<HR width=580 align=left>
</center>
<!--TEXT TABLE----------------------------------------------------------------------------------->

<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=580><TR><TD>
<FONT FACE="MS SERIF">
<p>
<br>
<center><i>NUCLEAR WASTE SHIPMENT UNDERWAY</i></center>

<p>  The nuclear waste shipment was prepared at the La Hague
         plutonium "reprocessing" factory near Cherbourg (France). 
<p>  The transport involving two casks holding 40 glass blocks of extremely radioactive
         nuclear waste containing some 20,500,000 curies of radioactivity, left Cherbourg on Monday 13th January. 
<p>This glassified nuclear waste is so deadly that a person within one metre of a single unshielded
         glass block would receive a fatal dose of radiation in less than one
         minute. 
<p>
<br>
<center><i>GREENPEACE PROTEST AT CHERBOURG AS "PACIFIC TEAL" DEPARTS FOR JAPAN</i>
<p>
<table>
	<tr>
		<td><a href="../pics/teal01.jpg"><img align=left width=150 height=97 border=0 		src="../thumbs/teal01t.jpg"></a></td>
		<td><a href="../pics/teal02.jpg"><img align=left width=150 height=97 border=0 		src="../thumbs/teal02t.jpg"></a></td>
		<td rowspan=2><a href="../pics/teal05.jpg"><img align=left width=86 height=150 		border=0 src="../thumbs/teal05t.jpg"></a></td>
	</tr>
		<td><a href="../pics/teal03.jpg"><img align=left width=150 height=97 border=0 		src="../thumbs/teal03t.jpg"></a>
		</td>
		<td><a href="../pics/teal04.jpg"><img align=left width=150 height=97 border=0 		src="../thumbs/teal04t.jpg"></a>
		</td>
	</tr>	
</table>	
</center></font>

<p><a href="maps.html">Route Map:</a> &nbsp World map showing likely and possible sea routes for the radioactive shipment
<br><br>


<hr>

<p> Greenpeace obtained a confidential document in December, which stated the second
            controversial plutonium waste shipment from Europe to Japan would leave
            France for Japan on 16th January 1997, on board the UK registered ship
            Pacific Teal. 
<p> The route for the ship is given as South Africa - east of
            Australia -south Pacific and finally Japan. 
<p>The document, which  authenticity has not been confirmed yet, also states that en-route
            governments are to be informed on 23rd December of the intended route of
            the waste. 

<p><a href="../pics/nfax.gif">The Original Document:</a> &nbsp <a href="nfax.html">The Translation:</a>
<hr>
</font>


<p><font size=+1><tt><a href="prjan14.html">Press Release:</a> &nbsp 14th January 1997 Nuclear waste shipment to go via South Africa and South Pacific.  This late announcement is an insult to en route states - says
Greenpeace</B></tt></font>

<p><font size=+1><tt><a href="prjan13.html">Press Release:</a> &nbsp 13th January 1997. Plutonium waste shipment leaves Cherbourg. Greenpeace warns en-route states of imminent threat</tt></font>

<p><font size=+1><tt><a href="prdec18.html">Press Release:</a> &nbsp 18th December 1996. Greenpeace releases confidential French government document on radioactive shipment route</tt></font>

<p><font size=+1><tt><a href="prdec09b.html">Press Release:</a> &nbsp 9th December 1996. New sea shipment of radioactive waste poses threat to health and environment, new report warns.</tt></font>

<p><font size=+1><tt><a href="prdec06.html">Press Release:</a> &nbsp 6th December 1996. Greenpeace will demand regional declaration in view of possible croosing of nuclear waste shipment</tt></font>

<p><font size=+1><tt><a href="prdec04.html">Press Release:</a> &nbsp 4th December 1996 Greenpeace sends ship to Caribbean to warn countries if imminent nuclear waste shipment.</tt></font>


 
</td></tr></table>
</td></tr></table>
