<html>
<head>
<title>Speeding up Java on the Greenpeace Homepage</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#ffffee" font size="+1" link="#008000" alink= "#000099" vlink="#139000">

<p>

<center><h2>Speeding up Java on the Greenpeace homepage
    </h2></center>
<p>
<blockquote>
<p>The Greenpeace Menu Applet is new, so we would very much appreciate any <a href="mailto:michiel@mcr1.poptel.org.uk?Subject=Greenpeace Applet Suggestion">Comments, Suggestions, or Bug-reports</a> you have.

<p>
If you access the Greenpeace homepage regularly it might be useful to download the classes for the Java applets and store them local on your computer. This will save you downloading the classes everytime you access the Greenpeace site. If you want to be informed of new classes to download, you can send a mail to <a href="mailto:michiel@mcr1.poptel.org.uk?Subject=Greenpeace Classes Update Request">michiel@mcr1.poptel.org.uk</a> with subject "Greenpeace Classes Update Request", or press <br>this button:
<form method=post content-type="text" action="mailto:michiel@mcr1.poptel.org.uk?Subject:Greenpeace+Classes+Update+Request">
<center><input type=Submit value="Inform Me of any Change in Classes at the Greenpeace Site"></center>
</form>
<hr>
<p><p>
<dl>
<dt><strong>UNIX</strong>
<dd>
<ul>
<li>the Greenpeace classes in UNIX format (Tarred and GZipped) can be downloaded <a href="/~michiel/gpcl.tar.gz">here</a>
<li>Create a subdirectory in your classes directory called <b>Greenpeace</b>
<li>Untar/zip these classes and put them the above directory
</ul><dt><hr><dd>

<dt><strong>DOS shell (Windows 95/NT)</strong>
<dd>
<ul>
<li>the Greenpeace classes in <a href="ftp://ftp2.winzip.com/winzip/winzip95.exe"><b>Winzip95</b></a> format can be downloaded <a href="/~michiel/gpcl.zip">here</a>
<li><dl><dt>Create a subdirectory called <b>Greenpeace</b> in your <i>classes</i> directory
	<dd>* <b>Netscape 3.0</B> and up: The classes directory is probably something like <br>C:\Program Files\Netscape\Navigator\Program\Java\Classes
	<dd>* <b>MSIE</b>: C:\Windows\Java\Classes
	</dl>
<li>Unzip the Greenpeace classes and put them in the above directory.
</ul>
<dt><hr><dd>

<dt><strong>MacOS</strong>
<dd><ul>
<li>the Greenpeace classes in Mac-format (BinHex) can be downloaded <a href="/~michiel/gpcl.hqx">here</a>
<li>Create a folder in <i>System Folder:Preferences:Netscape:Java</i> called <b>Greenpeace</b>
<li>Uncompress these classes and put them in the above folder
</ul>
<dt><hr><dd>
<dt><strong>DOS/Windows 3.1</strong>
<dd><ul>
<li>Unfortunately this will not work on an 8.3 system like Windows 3.1
</ul>
</dl>

</blockquote>
<p>

<hr size=4>
