<table border=0 cellpadding=7>
<tr><td align=center colspan=2><P><B>"Clearcutting causes two kinds of fundamental damage, one 
long-lasting, the other permanent.  The long-lasting damage is 
to the soil, the permanent damage is to biological diversity."</B> 
<BR><font size=-2>Dr. C. Pielou, Member of the Clayoquot Sound Science Panel</font></td></tr>
</table>


<table border=0 cellpadding=10>
<tr>

<td background color="ffffff"><FONT SIZE="+2"><b><I>LATEST NEWS: </I></b></font> 
<p><b>Greenpeace fight for Njakafjall forest, part of the almost untouched belt of Taiga
forest along the Swedish mountain chain.</b>
<p><a href=prfjan13.html><img src="../icons/bionews.gif" border=0 height=60 width=60 align=left> PRESS RELEASE:</a> January 13th, 1997 - Greenpeace wins the first round in the battle for Njakafjall
<br clear=all>
<p><a href=prfjan10.html><img src="../icons/bionews.gif" border=0 height=60 width=60 align=left>PRESS RELEASE:</a>
January 10th, 1997 - Greenpeace blocks logging in old growth forests

<br clear=all>
<p><b>October 22, 1996 - Greenpeace success: Enso will cease timber cutting in Karelian old growth forests. </b><br> The Finnish paper group Enso announced today that they will agree on a one year moratorium for timber cutting and timber sales in or from <A HREF="russia.html">Karelian or Murmansk old growthforests.</a> </td>

<td align=left width=350 height=250>
<!--MAP NAME="FOR_MAP2">
<AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="234,206,341,243" HREF="../cbio/newzea.html">
<AREA SHAPE="RECT" COORDS="288,163,345,205" HREF="../forestry/solomo.html">
