<html><head>
<title>MV Greenpeace Amazonian Expedition</title>
</head>

<body>
<h1>MV Greenpeace Amazonian Expedition</h1>

<a><IMG SRC="4decki.gif" alt="MV Greenpeace"></a>

During October 1994, the environmental ship MV Greenpeace made 
an expedition from the mouth of the Amazon up to the Rio Negro and 
thence back down to the Atlantic Ocean.  This trip was part of a
long campaign for the forests which took the ship from Siberia to British
Columbia to Central America to Brazil. The purpose of the 
journey was to publisise some of the many threats to the future of the 
forests in these areas.

<p>

While in Brazil, the activities of the MV Greenpeace included 
public outreach and non-violent direct actions to highlight 
the following issues.

<ul>

<li><A HREF="mercury.html">Water contamination from Mercury used in gold mining</A>

<li><A HREF="mahog.html">Forest destruction resulting from Mahogany export</A>

<li><A HREF="fldfrst.html">Logging in the Flooded Forests</A>

</ul>

<h3>Other Stuff</h3>

<ul>

<li><A HREF="brphoto.html">Photographs and audio from the expedition</A>

<li><A HREF="brothers.html">Links to other sites concerning forest issues</A>

<li>More information on the ship MV Greenpeace

</ul>

<HR>

